How much revenue is being generated by paying customers?

The team haven't released the product or UI yet - so the only users generating code are validators -plus a few people that will have copied the agent code into custom scaffolding to try it. 

I'm hoping the team can just plug into Cursor or fork VS Code for the first version of the product so there is not a huge development effort needed to get a first usable and billable product.

Not worth launching the product before the brain was built; so first priority on optimising the benchmark and speed of the agent iteration/improvement cycle made sense. 
I think the best agent is likely very close to good enough now though to be competitive and valuable to developers - even without much optimisation and packaging into a custom front end. 
Hopefully they can get V1 released soon!

In parallel - Chutes are also close to getting privacy fixed with TEE - so launching with that active (if Chutes will be the primary inference provider) has a much higher chance of getting momentum i think.
